      "content": "Exactly, it's like the nutrients are there, but the plant has a stubborn, microscopic barrier preventing it from accessing them—a very stubborn barrier, much like a grumpy, root-bound goblin guarding a pile of shiny bits! If your soil pH is off, you can adjust it by adding amendments. If the soil is too acidic, you can add lime to raise the pH, and if it's too alkaline, you might use elemental sulfur to lower it. Always follow the package directions for the amendments, and remember that these changes take time to fully integrate into the soil.",
